{{Italic title}} {{Taxobox | color = lightgrey | name = Acidipila dinghuensis | image = | image_caption = | regnum = [[Bacteria]] | phylum = [[Acidobacteria]] | classis = [[Acidobacteria]] | ordo = [[Acidobacteriales]] | familia = [[Acidobacteriaceae]] | genus = ''[[Acidipila]]'' | species = '''''A. dinghuensis''''' | binomial = ''Acidipila dinghuensis'' | binomial_authority = Jiang et al. 2016<ref name=Acidipila-dinghuensis>{{cite journal|last1=Parte|first1=A.C.|title=Acidipila|journal=Www.bacterio.net|url=http://www.bacterio.net/acidipila.html}}</ref> | type_strain = DHOF10, CGMCC 1.13007, KCTC 42631<ref name=UniProt/> | subdivision = | synonyms = Acidipila chinensis<ref name=UniProt>{{cite journal|title=Acidipila dinghuensis|journal=Www.uniprot.org|url=https://www.uniprot.org/taxonomy/1560006}}</ref> }}
'''''Acidipila dinghuensis''''' is a [[chemoorganotrophic]], [[Aerobic organism|aerobic]] and non-motile bacterium from the genus of [[Acidipila]] which has been isolated from the forest of [[Dinghushan Biosphere Reserve]] in the [[Guangdong Province]] in [[China]].<ref name=Acidipila-dinghuensis/><ref name=UniProt/><ref>{{cite journal|last1=Chen|first1=Mei-hong|last2=Lv|first2=Ying-ying|last3=Qiu|first3=Li-hong|last4=Wang|first4=Jia|last5=Jiang|first5=Ya-wen|title=Acidipila dinghuensis sp. nov., an acidobacterium isolated from forest soil|journal=International Journal of Systematic and Evolutionary Microbiology|date=1 January 2016|volume=66|issue=1|pages=76–83|doi=10.1099/ijsem.0.000676|pmid=26475169}}</ref>
