{{Infobox supercluster | name = Leo Supercluster | image = | credit = | epoch = | constellation = [[Ursa Major]], [[Leo (constellation)|Leo]] | ra = | dec = | brightest_member = [[Abell 1185]]<ref name="Kopylova"/> | member_no = | major_axis_mpc = 130 megaparsecs<ref name="Kopylova"/> | minor_axis_mpc = 60 megaparsecs<ref name="Kopylova"/> | redshift = 0.037<ref name="Kopylova"/> | distance = | mass = | luminosity = | flux = | other_names = }} The '''Leo Supercluster''' is a [[supercluster]] in the Northern Celestial Hemisphere that stretches across the constellations [[Ursa Major]] and [[Leo (constellation)|Leo]]. It covers an area approximately 130 mega[[parsec]]s long by 60 megaparsecs wide. The [[redshift]]s of member [[galaxy cluster]]s range from 0.032 to 0.043. The brightest cluster in the system is [[Abell 1185]].<ref name="Kopylova"/>
