0px]] |- | 55.4–48.6 Ma | '''Genus:''' * ''[[Heptodon]]'' | | | Suspected to be the ancestor of modern [[tapirs]]. |[[File:Heptodon posticus.jpg|150px]] |- | 38–33.9 Ma | '''Genus:''' * ''[[Hesperocyon]]'' | | | The earliest known [[canid]]. |[[File:Hesperocyon Gregarius.jpg|150px]] |- | ??? Ma | '''Genus:''' * ''[[Eurymylus]]'' | | | The earliest known [[lagomorph]]. | |- | 52.5 Ma | '''Genus:''' * ''[[Onychonycteris]]'' | | | One of the two oldest known [[Monotypic taxon|monospecific]] genera of [[bat]]. | |- | 2 Ma | '''Species:''' * ''[[Ailuropoda microta]]'' | | | The earliest known member of the [[giant panda]] clade. | |- | 63–61.7Ma | '''Genus:''' * ''[[Purgatorius]]'' | | |Believed to be the earliest example of a [[primate]] or a proto-primate, a primatomorph precursor to the [[Plesiadapiformes]]. |[[File:Purgatorius BW.jpg|200px]] |- | 12.5–8.5 Ma | '''Genus:''' * ''[[Sivapithecus]]'' | | | This genus may have been the ancestor to the modern [[orangutan]]s. |[[File:Sivapithecus.jpg|150px]] |- | 16–8 Ma | '''Genus:''' * ''[[Kenyapotamus]]'' | | |A possible ancestor of living [[hippopotamid]]s. | |- | ?? Ma | '''Genus:''' * ''[[Eomanis]]'' | | |The earliest known true (and scaled) [[pangolin]]. |[[File:Eomanis waldi 1.JPG|150px]] |}
