[[Category:Scientific instrument makers]]

[[File:Cerium(IV) oxide.jpg|206px|thumb|right|[[Cerium(IV) oxide|Cerium oxide]] is a potent mixed conductor.<ref name="MPG" />]] '''Mixed conductor''' which is known as '''mixed ion-electron conductor''' '''(MIEC)''' refers to a single phase material which has a significant [[Electrical conductor|conduction]] [[Ionic compound|ionic]]ally and [[electron]]ically.<ref name="MPG">{{cite web | url=http://www.fkf.mpg.de/2698712/MixedConductors | title=Mixed conductors | publisher=Max Planck institute for solid state research | accessdate=16 September 2016}}</ref><ref name="Riess">{{cite journal | url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0167273802001820 | title=Mixed ionic–electronic conductors—material properties and applications | author=I. Riess | journal=Solid State Ionics | year=2003 | volume=157 | issue=1-4 | pages=1–17 | doi=10.1016/S0167-2738(02)00182-0}}</ref><ref name="Nature">{{cite journal | url=http://www.nature.com/nature/journal/v536/n7615/full/nature19078.html | title=Synergistic, ultrafast mass storage and removal in artificial mixed conductors |author1=Chia-Chin Chen |author2=Lijun Fu |author3=Joachim Maier | journal=Nature | year=2016 | volume=536 | issue=7615 | pages=159–164 | doi=10.1038/nature19078|bibcode=2016Natur.536..159C }}</ref> Due to the '''mixed conduction''', a formally neutral species can transport in a [[solid]] and therefore mass storage and redistribution are enabled. Mixed conductors are well known in conjugation with [[High-temperature superconductivity]] and are able to capacitate rapid [[solid state chemistry|solid-state reaction]]s. They are used as [[catalyst]]s (for oxidation), [[permeation membrane]]s, [[sensor]]s and [[electrode]] in [[Battery (electricity)|batteries]] since they allow for rapidly transducing chemical signals and permeating chemical components.<ref name="Nature" /> [[Strontium titanate]] (SrTiO<sub>3</sub>), [[Titanium oxide]] (TiO<sub>2</sub>), (La,Ba, Sr)(Mn,Fe,Co)O<sub>3−d</sub>, La2CuO<sub>4+d</sub>, [[Cerium(IV) oxide]] (CeO<sub>2</sub>), [[Lithium iron phosphate]] (LiFePO<sub>4</sub>) and LiMnPO<sub>4</sub> are the examples for the mixed conductors.<ref name="MPG" />
